      <section eId="sec_10_7_40">
        <num>10-7-40</num>
        <content>
          <p>A surety or endorser is entitled to the process of attachment against his principal before payment of the debt under the same circumstances as any other creditor.</p>
          <p>(Orig. Code 1863, § 2138; Code 1868, § 2133; Code 1873, § 2160; Code 1882, § 2160; Civil Code 1895, § 2979; Civil Code 1910, § 3551; Code 1933, § 103-301.)</p>
